{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove the right for convicted sex offenders to appeal their sentence",
        "additional_details": "I wish for the law to be changed and for convicted perpetrators to have no right of appeal once sentencing has been passed. I believe that allowing them to appeal can cause more trauma and emotional upset to their victims.",
        "background": "As the law stands convicted sex offenders and child predators are entitled to appeal their sentences should they feel the sentencing is to harsh. I wish to remove their right to appeal their sentences.",
